The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Uco share issue
                                                                                                               Uco share issue
                            
	Mumbai, Sept. 17 (PTI): Uco Bank will raise Rs 2,250 crore through preferential shares to the government and qualified institutional buyers.        
	Shareholders of the bank have approved the plan of allotting perpetual non-cumulative preference shares on a private basis to the government and to various entities, Calcutta-based Uco said in a filing to the Bombay Stock Exchange.        
	The bank has got approval to allot 70,000 such shares aggregating Rs 700 crore to the government. The company would also raise up to Rs 1,550 crore from various entities on a private placement basis. Shares of Uco Bank today closed at Rs 46.80 on the BSE, down 0.53 per cent from its previous close.        
	In a similar move, Axis Bank has started the process of raising funds through private placement, an exercise estimated to raise over Rs 5,000 crore. A committee of directors, authorised by the banks board, took this decision at its meeting today, Axis Bank said in a disclosure to the Bombay Stock Exchange.                                                                                                                                       
